<handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                       <seg type="script"><date>Second half of the 13th/first half of the 14th-century</date> script.</seg> 
                       <date notBefore="1350" notAfter="1449"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                       <seg type="rubrication">One to three lines at the beginning of prayers, sometimes alternating with black lines; 
                         every second character, alternating with black characters, of the beginning of the prayer on <locus target="#101rb"/>
                         the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሌሉያ፡</foreign>; names of the letters of the Hebrew alphabet;
                         elements of punctuation marks and text dividers.</seg>
                       <desc>Careful, slightly irregular; by a good scribe. Both variants of the 6th-order ሰ can be found, the one constructed 
                         of a short horizontal stroke (ending with a serif) 
                         directed to the left, set up at the short oblique stroke, and the standard medieval/modern ስ (see e.g.<locus target="#24v #25r"/> against <locus target="#20r"/>).
                         The word for God is written both as one and as two units (see e.g. <locus target="#20r"/>). 
                         The hand is similar to that of <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet25">Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 25</ref> or the last hand of <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum050">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, ʿUrā Qirqos, UM-050</ref>
                       </desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>

<additions>
  <list>
    <item xml:id="e1">
      <locus target="#4r"/>
      <desc><foreign xml:lang="gez">ማቴዎስ፡</foreign> is written in the upper margin, possibly by the main hand.</desc>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="e2">
      <locus target="#57va #76vb"/>
      <desc>The name <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13957Qalementos">Qalemǝnṭos</persName>, possibly identical with a person of the same name attested in
        <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SinaiEt004">Sinai Peninsula, Saint Catherine’s Monastery Sinai, Sinai Ethiopic 4</ref> and <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SinaiEt006">Sinai Peninsula, Saint Catherine’s Monastery Sinai, Sinai Ethiopic 6</ref>,
        is mentioned in supplications within the main body of the text.</desc>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a1">
      <desc>Note on the inner front board, only partly visible.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez">ኤና ከ ትረያ
      ወረሀ፡ ታሕሳስ፡ እም ፲
      ገብዐከ</q>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a2">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Note in brownish ink in the upper margin, only partly visible.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez">ለጸ<gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="1"/> ነሀናሰርበመንገክርስቶ ዐሜን </q>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a3">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Note in brownish ink in the lower margin, only partly visible.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez">ተዘከሮ ለሀብርኮ ናሰር ወ<add place="below">ለ</add>ዕ<gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ና
      ሰርበ፡ መንገሰተ ሰማያት ዐሜን</q>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a4">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Note in faded ink in the left margin, only partly visible.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez">ዕምሰሙ
      <gap reason="illegible"/>ታሕሳስ</q>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a5">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>List of numbers under Gǝnbot and Sane.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez"/>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a6">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Possibly pen trial, the characters መ and እ are repeated in several orders.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez"/>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a7">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Erased note.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez"/>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a8">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Prayer.</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez"/>
    </item>
    
    <item xml:id="a9">
      <locus target="#112v"/>
      <desc>Prayer in faded ink (beginning identical as above).</desc>
      <q xml:lang="gez">እግዚእየ፡ ወአምላክየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ እግዚአ፡ ብሔር፡ ሕያው፡ ዘእምኃቤሁ፡ ኵሉ፡ ሃብት፡ ወሠናያት፡ አበ፡ ብርሃናት፡ ዘይሁብ፡
        <gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="2"/>ለኅሩያኒሁ<gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="2"/>ምላእ፡ ላዕሌነ
      </q>
    </item>
    
  </list>
</additions>
